<TITLE> Jamuna enters capital market Jan9, Meghna Jan14 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com)State-run enterprises Jamuna Oil and Meghna Petroleum will enter the capital market in January, DSE officials said Thursday, as the listing agreements were signed between the two companies and the Dhaka Stock Exchange. The inaugural trading dates of Jamuna and Meghna are Jan 9 and Jan 14 respectively. Jamuna will raise Tk 135 million by offloading 13.5 million ordinary shares of Tk 10 each. Meghna will offer 12 million ordinary shares at Tk 10 each to raise Tk 120 million from the capital market. At a DSE-organised press conference Thursday, power and energy adviser Tapan Chowdhury said the capital market plays an important role in a country's industrialisation. He also said that the government had further initiatives for SOEs, under the power, energy and mineral resources ministry, to be listed on the capital market. Securities and Exchange Commission chairman Faruq Ahmad Siddiqi said that the last year was "very significant" for the capital market with indices scaling record heights. He thanked the government for offloading shares at a time when the market is overwhelmed with demand for new issues. DSE senior vice president Ahmad Rashid Lali also announced the proposed launch of Titas Gas Transmission in the capital marketand thanked the government, the Investment Corporation of Bangladesh and all concerned for the long awaited listing of Jamuna and Meghna. Energy secretary Mohammad Mohsin said the next six months would see more government entities under the power ministry offloading shares on the capital market and assured investors of the profitability of the state-run oil companies, Jamuna and Meghna. bdne
